WEBVTT



00:00:00.704 --> 00:00:10.752
Hello, and thank you for listening to Desiring God's Messages podcast. This is Tony Reinke, host of the Ask Pastor John podcast here today with an announcement on what's coming up for us at Desiring God.

00:00:10.272 --> 00:00:11.776
Aaron Godd in October. Thank you.

00:00:11.680 --> 00:00:16.160
It's a series we're calling Here We Stand. Here we stand.

00:00:16.352 --> 00:00:17.664
And to explain it,

00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:19.104
There's Pastor John.

00:00:25.152 --> 00:00:26.912
Five hundred years ago,

00:00:27.104 --> 00:00:31.840
A lowly German priest walked up to a church door in Wittenberg.

00:00:31.616 --> 00:00:33.824
And posted a document

00:00:33.888 --> 00:00:35.424
That altered

00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:37.056
The course of history.

00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:45.952
It has now been five centuries since Martin Luther stood up and confronted Roman Catholicism with the bright flame of the gospel.

00:00:45.888 --> 00:00:48.960
The kindling had been laid for decades.

00:00:49.120 --> 00:00:54.432
And Luther's little, almost accidental spark soon set all of Europe.

00:00:54.080 --> 00:00:55.552
A blaze.

00:00:55.648 --> 00:00:56.992
In time

00:00:56.992 --> 00:01:03.840
This lowly monk proved he had what it takes to hold his ground against the church and the world.

00:01:04.544 --> 00:01:09.248
And under God the sparks that flew from the anvil of his tongue,

00:01:09.152 --> 00:01:12.064
Lit the fires of a global reformation.

00:01:12.352 --> 00:01:15.040
In one especially memorable scene,

00:01:14.912 --> 00:01:20.512
He stood before the Emperor and declared courageously, risking his own life.

00:01:20.416 --> 00:01:22.080
Here I stand.

00:01:22.144 --> 00:01:23.808
I can do no other.

00:01:24.064 --> 00:01:25.728
So help me, God!

00:01:26.368 --> 00:01:29.312
But Luther did not stand alone.

00:01:29.568 --> 00:01:36.896
The Reformation was not about one or two or three big names, Luther, Calvin, Zwingli.

00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:41.632
But about a massive movement of Christian conviction, boldness.

00:01:41.536 --> 00:01:42.880
And joy!

00:01:42.976 --> 00:01:46.272
That cost many men and women their lives.

00:01:46.240 --> 00:01:52.384
And scattered the seeds of gospel truth that are still bearing eternal fruit in the twenty-first century.

00:01:52.800 --> 00:02:00.768
Not only was Luther surrounded by reformers in Germany and Switzerland, but lesser-known heroes of the faith rose up all over Europe.

00:02:01.056 --> 00:02:03.968
Heinrich Bullinger, Hugh Latimer,

00:02:03.744 --> 00:02:07.808
Lady Jane Grey, Theodore Beza, Johannes,

00:02:07.616 --> 00:02:09.440
Oculumpetius.

00:02:09.728 --> 00:02:12.288
Luther was the battering ram.

00:02:12.192 --> 00:02:14.592
But once the war was breached,

00:02:14.592 --> 00:02:18.592
The foot soldiers of the Reformation could not be stopped.

00:02:18.784 --> 00:02:20.768
And here we stand today.

00:02:20.608 --> 00:02:23.008
Five hundred years later,

00:02:23.008 --> 00:02:27.584
Luther wasn't alone then, and he's not alone now.

00:02:27.744 --> 00:02:32.704
We've created a series of 31 short biographies.

00:02:32.544 --> 00:02:35.328
One for every day in October.

00:02:35.424 --> 00:02:38.464
The podcast is produced by Desiring God,

00:02:38.432 --> 00:02:41.824
In partnership with Bethlehem College and Seminary.

00:02:42.592 --> 00:02:51.904
If you want to learn more about the Reformation and be inspired by Christian heroes, men and women, famous and almost unknown,

00:02:52.256 --> 00:02:55.232
Subscribe to Huey Stand or visit

00:02:55.264 --> 00:02:58.368
Desiring God org forward slash

00:02:58.272 --> 00:02:59.488
Stand.

00:02:59.552 --> 00:03:03.712
Consider the word of the Lord in Hebrews, thirteen, seven.

00:03:03.584 --> 00:03:05.472
Remember your leaders.

00:03:05.504 --> 00:03:08.352
Those who spoke to you the word of God.

00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:09.760
Consider

00:03:09.504 --> 00:03:12.160
The outcome of their way of life.

00:03:12.096 --> 00:03:13.696
And imitate.

00:03:13.664 --> 00:03:14.944
Their faith.

00:03:17.472 --> 00:03:21.472
Amen. DesiringGod.org forward slash stand. Thank you.

00:03:21.312 --> 00:03:30.016
Is the web address or just go to our site DesiringGone.org and click on the banner at the top of the screen. However you get there, I hope you will join us in October.

00:03:30.080 --> 00:03:31.584
For here we stand.
